Opened in the mid-2000s, this JD Wetherspoon lies beneath apartment accommodation. The name comes from the proximity of the pub to the former railway line (the adjacent Sainsbury's cafe is in the former station building) that once served the area. A large space has been made to appear more intimate by breaking up the space with columns, artefacts and good lighting. Although the location is in the middle of a student area, the pub attractive to a wide range of customers. Usually five or six cask beers on.
